window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>She's a corporate lawyer; he's a carefree bodyguard. When their worlds collide, sparks fly in 'About That One Night'—a romantic comedy about opposites attracting in the most delightful way.</i><br> <br> Life doesn't always go as planned, but sometimes, that's where the magic happens.<br> <br> <i>Enter me: Zoe Harper.</i></p> <p>Let me tell you, life has a funny way of flipping you upside down when you least expect it.</p> <p>Case in point: I’m currently packing up my life into cardboard boxes after leaving my long-term, commitment-phobic ex-boyfriend.</p> <p>Just when I think things can’t get worse, I find myself at a destination wedding with a grumpy but ridiculously handsome bodyguard, Maximillian McCallister.</p> <p>Max and I have always been frenemies: he’s annoyingly charming, and I’m just trying to figure out my next move without losing my mind.</p> <p>But one night, fueled by tequila and maybe a little bit of spite, we end up having the most incredible one-night stand. It changes <i>everything</i>.</p> <p>Now I’m back in Boston, trying to figure out my new life with my meddling family, my stressful career, and stupidly hot Max popping up everywhere I go.</p> <p>He’s infuriatingly perfect, and did I mention he’s my brother-in-law’s best friend? Yeah, it’s complicated. Even before factoring in the positive pregnancy test that flips my world upside down.</p>"; 
